        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'><b>Easy! Here is the short version of how I did it (just to show you how easy it was):</b></P><P>Get up to air, buy Key of Swords, give Thunder spirit Princess 3pp, use Key to come to Noble Dojorn island (also known as monk epic island), get your friend to knock you over to Gorgalask island. Done.</P><P><b>Here is the detailed version:</b></P><P>1. Find someone who has the Cetari Wardstaff or the BFG.</P><P>2. Get PoA stones in Erudin.</P><P>3. Get a wizzy friend to port you up with the guy who has Chetari Staff or BFG.</P><P>4. When on PoA, buy the Key of Swords from the Key Master fellow. (the most expensive one) and give your friend with the staff/BFG pp so he can buy it too. Kick the wizzy off PoA - he is not needed anymore.</P><P>5. Give Thunder Spirit Princess 3pp to spawn Gzzkallk.</P><P>6. Use Key of Swords so that you and your friend end up on the island with Noble Dojorn and the Bladestorms.</P><P>7. Stand on the edge, face the island with the Gorgalasks and the windmill, look upwards. This island is a little bit below the island you are standing on.</P><P>8. /duel your friend. Let him a) right click his BFG or b) swing his Chetari Wardstaff and proc the Knockback on you.</P><P>You will then flyyyyyy over to the Gorgalask island and fall for about 200dmg (won't be more since the actual height isn't that much). You won't be KoS but I FD'ed just in case anyway as soon as I landed... and there go to Gzzalllk and hand him the Book.</P><P>Now you just have to go to Lake Rathe to get your Scythe!</P><P>After getting a friend with the staff and a wiz and the skystone, the trip itself took me about 15 minutes. So it is fast & easy!</P><P>Nothing aggros either! Why kill the azeracs when you don't need to ;)</P><P>Piece of cake. Noble Dojorn might aggro your friend hitting you though, but it was not a problem for me since my Chetari Wardstaff friend didn't actually hit me... cause he sucks :P He just procced the staff.</P><P><font size=-2>Sick with suffering. The stench and filth of him. Death all around him. The flies, the dogs, the din. King of death and pain. Ruler of the slain. Bleak horror. His kingdom of the ghost. <b>.Vermis.Mysteriis.Defiler.<BR></b><BR></font></P><P>Edited by - Vermis Mysteriis on 12/17/2001  06:47:23</font></td>
